main event: A witness observed a bright, triangular-shaped object traveling at high speed from east to west in Pennsylvania in 1963.
interesting points: The object was brilliantly lit and made a strong impression on the witness.
The witness was an ex-pilot with 9 years of experience in the Air Force.
The object was observed for approximately 25-30 minutes.
The witness was familiar with both satellites and aircraft, and stated that the object had none of the characteristics of either.
The object was also witnessed by the witness's wife and a friend.
witnesses: a witness, his wife, and a friend
